Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
• From the balance sheet, total liabilities equal Total Assets minus Total Owner’s Equity.  
  Total Liabilities = 19,501,451.49 – 16,111,731.83 = 3,389,719.66  
• Then, Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 3,389,719.66 / 19,501,451.49  
  ≈ 0.17385, which we round to 0.17  

Step 2: Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio.  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –4,504,752.68  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 111,731.83  
• The ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Net Profit  
  = (–4,504,752.68) / 111,731.83  
  ≈ –40.32  

Thus, the solution is:
